node.text: üé∂THE HILLS ARE ALIIIIIIIVE üé∂ Can you believe this is #Italy?! I used to think that Sicily was the most different part of Italy, but not anymore ‚Äî #AltoAdige is. This region in the northeast has been passed back and forth between Italy and Austria many times over the centuries, and as a result, it more resembles Austria, Germany, or Switzerland. ‚õ∞ This is one of the 11 things that I learned on my latest trip to Italy ‚Äî and guess what, that‚Äôs a blog post I published today! Click on the link in my profile to find out the other 10. #dolomites #southtyrol üåà Have you been to Alro Adige?

I am home, home, home. üíï Three weeks in #Italy have come to a close. A country I adore; a country I never tire of visiting. I also did a bit of an Instagram experiment ‚Äî I wanted to see if I could take a good, Instagram-worthy photo of myself every day I was there. And I did (plus this pro photo shoot in #Florence with @alexandrajitariuc). While taking photos of yourself is possibly while traveling solo, it‚Äôs a LOT easier and faster when you have friends with you. I enjoyed it. I‚Äôll probably do more of it. üíï I‚Äôm so Italy-enamored, I plan to get a post out about it tomorrow on the blog. Stay tuned for that. üáÆüáπ Did you enjoy the 21 days of photos of me, or do you prefer photos of scenery and stuff?

Say hey to your gargoyle for me. üòú The first two times I went to #Milan, I only stayed for 24 hours and barely saw any of it. This time I had five days to soak it up ‚Äî but I‚Äôll be honest, as this is the end of a three-week trip, I spent a lot of the time chilling and catching up on work. But I had always wondered about Milan ‚Äî it‚Äôs 1) a big city 2) in Italy 3) with great flight connections. Is this a place where I could live? ü§î After enjoying aperitivos and gelato, taking the tram around the city, and trying to genuinely get a sense of what makes Milan tick, I think I COULD live here if necessary ‚Äî but the burning desire just isn‚Äôt there. It‚Äôs fun to visit, though, and I‚Äôd be happy to add a few days onto the end of a trip next time. But my heart still belongs to Bologna, a city that just radiates warmth and joy. üáÆüáπ If you had to live somewhere in Italy, where would it be?

Is it true that #Milan is a fashionable town? Um YEP. üò≥ Last night I went out for aperitivo in a cool part of the city with some local friends and I was blown away by how well everyone was dressed! The men more than the women. Tight fitted suits, perfectly coiffed hair...I felt like such a schlub by comparison! ü§£ Today I finally saw the top item on my Milan bucket list: The Last Supper. What a painting ‚Äî it was incredible to see it. The Last Supper sells out months in advance so I went on a tour with @walkstours that included The Last Supper and a tour of Milan‚Äôs Duomo, including the rooftop. The last time I saw the Duomo, 15 years ago, it was covered in scaffolding, so this was so much better! Thanks for comping me, @walkstours. üáÆüáπ Tomorrow is my last full day in #Italy (well, at least until September) ‚Äî what should I do? Besides eat a ton of gelato?

Train life. üöÑ Trains are my favorite way to travel #Italy, and while they‚Äôre not perfect for EVERYWHERE, they cover a ton of the country. Plus they‚Äôre exceedingly pleasant, especially my favorite train, the #Frecciarossa, the high speed train. Huge thanks to @italiarail for comping me two first class Italy rail passes for this trip and allowing me to zip around at 300 kph with ease. You need to book reservations for the high speed trains, but it‚Äôs only ‚Ç¨10 per train and first class is SOOOOOO nice. The seats are luxurious and they give you free drinks and snacks (including wine ‚Äî this is Italy after all). I found out yesterday there‚Äôs actually a direct Frecciarossa from Torino, in the far northwest, to Lecce, in the far southeast. It takes 11.5 hours and that‚Äôs one ride I wouldn‚Äôt mind taking! Next time. üöÑ Have you traveled Italy by train?

This is the best chocolatey beverage you‚Äôve never heard of ‚Äî the #bicerin! ‚òïÔ∏è The bicerin ‚Äî pronounced BEE-chih-REEN ‚Äî is from the city of #Torino, which I am exploring today. It‚Äôs a combination of hot chocolate and coffee topped with a cream floater. It‚Äôs delicious ‚Äî and if you‚Äôre starting to feel sleepy, this will give you the rush you need to keep up sightseeing! ‚ú® I had mine at Cafe Al Bicerin, which dates back to 1763 and feels like a time capsule. I highly recommend stopping there on a trip to Torino, but I‚Äôd love to try other cafes to see if they have a unique twist on it! Torino is a lovely city and it was a super-easy day trip from Milan: just one hour on the high-speed Frecciarossa train. #italy üáÆüáπ Have you ever had a bicerin? Does it look like something you‚Äôd try?

Everything on Instagram is insanely posed, but this is the closest to how I actually look on a normal day. Clutching my camera. No lipstick because I‚Äôll inevitably smear it all over the camera screen and thus all over my face. Fake leather moto jacket on top of whatever dress I *think* will look good, and frankly, I‚Äôm rolling the dice. Oh, and let‚Äôs not forget the shoes that are completely impractical for climbing a mountain because I thought there were steps to the top! (There are not.) But you know what? These pics are just as real as any of the posed ones. And this was a seriously cool spot (#Mottarrone) ‚Äî on a clear day you can see seven of Italy‚Äôs lakes! I counted five. #piemonte #italia #photographerlife ‚ú® What are you getting up to this week?

#ThisIs34. üòâ I‚Äôm in the closing months of being 34 years old, and enjoying every minute of it. I have yet to reach an age that I am genuinely uncomfortable to be, and even though turning 35 in August will@push me into a new age bracket, I‚Äôm embracing it. Aging is a privilege. There are always new and exciting adventures ahead. ‚ú® I‚Äôve had the most beautiful two days in Lake Orta ‚Äî I need to come back here someday! ü¶ã How old are you now and how do you feel?

Everyone is familiar with Lake Como, but there are even better lakes in this part of #Italy ‚Äî like #LakeMaggiore in #Piedmont. This immense lake is pure glamour. I only wish I had come a few months ago when the mountains were capped with snow! So beautiful. If you‚Äôre coming here, I recommend checking out the small town of #Stresa and taking the ferry to the islands. Stresa has some good restaurants and Wes Anderson-looking hotels. It‚Äôs definitely not as busy or as famous here as Lake Como. And if you stick around, there are even quieter lakes to explore ‚Äî like Lake Orta, where I just arrived for the next two days. üòâ #piemonte #lagodimaggiore üáÆüáπ Do you have a special lake you‚Äôve discovered on your travels?

Confession time ‚Äî ever used #Tinder on your travels? I have. Not often, but enough to make things interesting. üíï If you‚Äôre traveling solo, meeting someone via Tinder can be a great way to gain insight into the culture. üç∑ And once when I was in Guatemala with one of my tours, my girls and I used Tinder to invite as many guys as possible to meet up with us at a bar. ü§£ But MOST interesting is when you go to a conference full of your friends and colleagues whom you adore but see rarely, and use Tinder just to see who‚Äôs single and looking at the moment. üòà Thinking of using it? Go for it. Just make sure that someone you trust knows your plans and check in with him or her. ‚ú® Have you used Tinder or other dating apps on your travels?

The #Dolomites really do deliver. ‚õ∞ For my final day at @ciasasalares in #SouthTyrol, I went on a hike into the mountains! HOW GORGEOUS IS THIS?! We literally started on the ground by the hotel and climbed on and on and on. üßóüèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è I held up surprisingly well ‚Äî last time I hiked at altitude, in Vail, I was exhausted at the mildest exertions. This was just fun ‚Äî and stunning. When you walk to the top, you have a 360-degree view of jagged peaks. I felt like Maria in The Sound of Music! üç∑ Some wine and cacio e pepe later and a dip in the hot tub were DEFINITELY earned! ‚ú® Thanks to the Ciasa Salares staff for making it such a beautiful stay. Today @cailinoneil and I are on a 8.5-hour journey by van, bus, and four trains to Lake Como. So excited to see the scenery tomorrow! #altoadige #italy #italia üáÆüáπ Where is your favorite place to hike?

Find someone who looks at you the way I look at cured meats. üòç Last night @cailinoneil and I had the ultimate dining experience here at @ciasasalares in the Dolomites ‚Äî wine tasting in the gorgeous cellar, with strange and wonderful wines from Calabria, Venezia Giulia, Emilia, and more. We finished with fondue ‚Äî both meat and cheese! And then a visit to the CHOCOLATE ROOM, which is exactly what it sounds like (see my Stories for me singing the Willy Wonka song). Honestly, the speck here in Alto Adige is far and beyond the usual prosciutto ‚Äî I cant get enough of it. It‚Äôs feathery and smoky. And the wines are GORGEOUS. This culinary mountain retreat has been exactly what we needed. Truthfully, we both arrived here sick as a dog after too much conference, but after two days here we are nearly recovered. Fun fact: one of the wines was called ‚ÄúInsolente,‚Äù which is Italian for dickhead!üç∑ What‚Äôs your favorite wine?

The #Dolomites are MAGICAL. ‚õ∞ Today I went on a tour of the region with @ciasasalares and I enjoyed the gorgeous peaks, wood cabins, and chocolate box-like villages. This region delivers on every front ‚Äî and my friends in Emilia-Romagna night kill me for saying this, but the local form of prosciutto here, speck, is TRANSCENDENTLY GOOD. I nearly died. ‚ú® Tomorrow is all about the hiking. Check out some more videos from the Dolomites on my Stories! üáÆüáπ What are you up to this fine Tuesday?

Hello #Dolomites! üòç After the insanity of #Traverse19, I knew I would need to relax and recover ‚Äî so @cailinoneil and I headed to @ciasasalares. This is the view from our sweet balcony! This resort is gorgeous and looks far more like something in Austria or Germany than in #Italy! It‚Äôs not a surprise ‚Äî this Italian region, #SouthTyrol or #AltoAdige, has a long history of being passed back and forth between the two countries, and both German and Italian are spoken here, as well as the local language Ladin. Over the next few days we will be exploring the gorgeous mountain landscapes, eating delicious food, and soaking up the spa. Just what we need after four days of parties, networking, and too little sleep. I can‚Äôt wait! üëö This top is by @dereklam (man do I love that brand) and the sunglasses are @tomford as always. ‚õ∞ Have you been to the Dolomites?

What are your feelings on...gelato? üç® When I first went to #Italy during my semester abroad in 2004, I got into the habit of having gelato every day. I still do almost every day when I‚Äôm back. It‚Äôs so much better than regular ice cream ‚Äî and it‚Äôs cheap and served in small portions! ‚ú® Here are some tips: look for a gelateria with metal tins, the gelato isn‚Äôt piled up super high, the banana is gray, and the pistachio is brownish. If you follow that advice, you‚Äôve probably found a decent gelato place. Here in #Trento I loved the gelato at a place called Gelateria Cherry. üç¶ My favorite flavors? I love the combo of limone and lampone (lemon and raspberry), but I‚Äôm always up for stracciatella (chocolate chip) or fragola (strawberry). #visittrentino #Traverse19 What‚Äôs your favorite gelato flavor?

Romance on #LakeGarda. üòç My little excursion to the town of #RivaDelGarda yesterday was one of the highlights of my time in #Trentino and all of #Italy! The lake is SO impressive ‚Äî wild, windy, and surrounded by enormous mountains. It simultaneously feels like the Alps and the tropics ‚Äî such a cool place! I had barely heard of Lake Garda before this trip, even having traveled extensively in Italy, but now it‚Äôs one of my favorite nature destinations in the country. Trentino, you are a superstar. I can‚Äôt believe how much you have to offer. #Traverse19 ‚õ∞üå¥ What destination surprised you?

#Trentino, you are SO pretty ‚Äî even when you make my hair crazy! ü§£ Today my friends and I road tripped down to #LakeGarda! This enormous lake is surrounded by tall mountains, while palm trees dot the landscape ‚Äî it‚Äôs an interesting mix! ‚õ∞üå¥ We visited the town of #RivaDelGarda, which is pastel-perfect. It reminded me a lot of Liguria, even though we are far from the sea! We climbed 165 steps to the top of the tower and the view was outstanding. I wish I had more time to explore Lake Garda, and I‚Äôm curious to see how it compares to Lake Como and Lake Maggiore later in the trip. #visittrentino #Traverse19 üåà Have you been to Lake Garda? Or anywhere that has both mountains and palm trees?

Greetings from #Trentino, #Italy! How gorgeous are these mountains?! üòç I‚Äôm here in the city of #Trento (as in Trent, as in yes, the Council of Trent ‚Äî remember that?) for the #Traverse19 conference, where I‚Äôll be speaking about the most important things I‚Äôve learned in my nine-year professional travel blogging career. Today we took the cable car to the top of the mountain and enjoyed this splendid view! ‚õ∞ So far, Trento feels cozy, unpretentious and low-key. The perfect spot to sit at an outdoor table with friends drinking cassis spritzes! üçπ I‚Äôm so looking forward to what the next few days bring. Tomorrow I am exploring Trento and hope to get to Lake Garda. You can follow along in real time on my Stories! ‚ú® And hell yes, I‚Äôm rocking the @voodoovixenldn overalls from @uniquevintage. I LOVE THESE SO DAMN MUCH. #visittrentino üíï What are you getting up to this weekend?

Every time I go to #Italy, without failure, I start dreaming of owning a #Vespa. üõµ How amazing would it be to cruise the streets of Manhattan on one of these? Well, let‚Äôs be honest. New York is too gross for Vespa riding...and part of me dreams of moving to Italy again. I love the lifestyle here and the cost of living is SO much lower. I mean, good bottles of wine for ‚Ç¨4? Aperitivo buffets with a fancy cocktail for under ‚Ç¨15? Pizza for ‚Ç¨5? üç∑ Maybe I‚Äôll make the move someday, to well-connected Milan or my beloved Bologna. Until then, I‚Äôll visit as often as I can. üì∏ Yesterday I booked a photo shoot in #Florence to commemorate 15 years since my semester abroad. The lovely @alexandrajitariuc took portraits of me all over the trendy Santo Spirito neighborhood. I am VERY happy with them ‚Äî not least because I look a million times better at 34 than I did at 20! Never forget what a cruel time the early 2000s were to fashion. üáÆüáπ Where do you dream of moving someday?

Greetings from #Florence, #Italy! üé® What a trip it is to be back here -- I studied abroad here 15 years ago in 2004! This is my first trip back since 2006, and WOW, is it a different place. It‚Äôs got golf carts and WiFi and an Apple store. ‚ú® Honestly, don‚Äôt come here in the high season at all (which it is now) ‚Äî it‚Äôs just WAY too crowded and dominated by tourists. You can barely move in the city center. It makes me feel lucky for experiencing Florence as a 20-year-old because I didn‚Äôt know any better ‚Äî I just thought it was amazing. And to be fair, the artistic treasures here are sublime ‚Äî it‚Äôs just that Florence is a little too small to contain all these tourists. I‚Äôm glad I came back to see it, but I don‚Äôt think I‚Äôll be back unless I have a VERY good reason. Today my heart belongs to cities like Bologna where you can just chill among the locals and get spoken to in Italian first, not English. üçπ I have to admit I spent most of today tracking down my old haunts ‚Äî some of the awful Irish pubs I frequented still exist, like JJ‚Äôs and The Old Stove. And I had to have pizza at the restaurant across from my old apartment, Le Collinine, now called Oinos. See more on my Stories today. üåà Did you study abroad? Did you ever go back?

Did you know that #Bologna is the best food city in #Italy? Even Italians in other cities grudgingly concede that Bologna and the surrounding #EmiliaRomagna region do food better than anywhere else. üçù Today I went to my favorite Bologna restaurant, Osteria dell‚ÄôOrsa, with my friend @domestiphobia, and had my favorite dish, tagliatelle rag√∫. This is the REAL dish spaghetti bolognese is based on, only a million times better. And at this cheap and cheerful place, it costs a lovely ‚Ç¨6.50. Go early to get a spot! üßÄ Emilia-Romagna is also the home of prosciutto di Parma, parmigiano reggiano, traditional balsamic vinegar from Modena, and all kinds of delicious produce, from truffles to chestnuts to heirloom tomatoes. And don‚Äôt forget to wash it all down with cold sparkling lambrusco! üç∑Come here hungry! #InEmiliaRomagna #Blogville üáÆüáπ What‚Äôs your favorite food region around the world?

What happens when a city you love ‚Äî BOLOGNA, ITALY ‚Äî changes? üíï #Bologna has been my favorite city in Italy for a long time ‚Äî I love the vibe, the food, the culture. And while I‚Äôve spent a ton of time here, I haven‚Äôt been back since 2013. Today when out for a walk, I was sad to see my favorite aperitivo bar and tiramisu spot were gone. And it felt surprising to see ramen, bibimbap and poke spots! And there are a ton of tour groups now, but considering how much work I‚Äôve been doing for Emilia-Romagna tourism since 2011, more tour groups just means I‚Äôve done my job! üëçüèº Colson Whitehead once said that you become a New Yorker when the New York you love starts disappearing amidst the new developments. It‚Äôs just a testament to how much you love the city. And Bologna is freaking amazing!!! I‚Äôm so happy to be here amongst the sunshine, the red walls, the 11 AM Lambrusco breaks, and the squacquerone cheese. See my Stories for much more of Bologna. #inEmiliaRomagna ‚ú® Have you ever returned to a place that changed?

For the first year after I moved to New York in 2016, I would cry every time I took an Uber to the airport. After years of traveling the world, I had finally chosen a place just for me. I loved my stationary life and didn‚Äôt want to leave it, even for somewhere awesome. I got over it, but sometimes I get a bit teary as I drive over Randall‚Äôs Island and watch the skyline go by. ‚ú® I won‚Äôt be crying when I fly out tonight. In part because I‚Äôm taking the subway (because there‚Äôs no way in hell I‚Äôm taking an Uber to JFK during rush hour on a Friday night, aka paying to be even more miserable). On to Italy. It‚Äôs going to be amazing. üì∏: @marijanamarinovic_mariachi

Have you ever been to the #Highline before? This elevated park in New York is a gorgeous place to take a walk! You stroll above the city and enjoy the greenery. And I kind of love gazing into the windows of the apartments that overlook it, wondering about the people who live there. Kind of weird to have your bed in plain view of so many people!! üå≥ The HighLine is debuting a new section on June 5 called the Spur, right by Hudson Yards. I got to preview it yesterday. It includes a gorgeous sculpture by Simone Leigh called Brick House: a sixteen-foot-tall bust of a black woman with cowrie shell-adorned braids. This new section is totally worth a visit ‚Äî come check it out from June 5 onwards! And head to Mercado Little Spain afterward for some jamon y queso. #HighlineSpur @highlinenyc ‚ú® I‚Äôm LOVING my new cropped fitted @voodoovixenldn overalls, which I got from @uniquevintage. SO DAMN CUTE. Got the striped top there too. üåà Have you been to the HighLine? What did you think?

FASHION. üì∏üëóüíã I loved this @dereklam dress so much that this weekend I hired photographer @marijanamarinovic_mariachi to do a photo shoot in #Soho! So glad to have some nice #NYC photos in my portfolio. üë† In the past year I‚Äôve really upped my fashion game. It makes a big difference in my photos and it just makes me so much happier! Thank you for capturing this, Marijana! ‚ú® Do watch my Stories today ‚Äî I have a new fashion show with the dresses I‚Äôm debating bringing to Italy. Go cast your vote! #yellowdress #newyorklife What are you excited about right now?

I used to think I was a beach person. Nope. I‚Äôm actually a mountains person. ‚õ∞ Beaches are nice and all, but nothing makes me as happy as seeing mountains spring up in all directions around me. This photo was taken in #Vail, #Colorado, in 2017 ‚Äî I absolutely loved the summer hiking there!! A few of my other favorite mountain destinations are the city of Innsbruck, Austria (where you are surrounded by mountains and you can take a funicular to the top for hiking), the White Mountains in New Hampshire (where I spent my summers camping growing up), and, believe it or not, Antarctica, which is covered with gorgeous mountains. This summer, I‚Äôm visiting the Dolomites for the first time and I can‚Äôt wait. üèï What about you? What‚Äôs your favorite mountain destination?

Kicking off summer in #Bushwick. üç∫ I have two more days with this fabulous yellow dress by @dereklam I rented for the month ‚Äî so I booked a pro photo shoot wearing it in SoHo yesterday! Can‚Äôt wait to see the results, which I should get in a few days. For now, here‚Äôs the after-shoot activity ‚Äî hanging at @brooklynbeergarden with @katrinkasasha on her annual visit from Istanbul. It‚Äôs a cool outdoor beer garden that serves exclusively Brooklyn beer and wine. I had no idea I‚Äôd find a mural that matched my dress! ‚ú® What are you up to this fine Sunday?

So, where are you spending Memorial Day weekend? I‚Äôm here in New York. ‚úåüèº No desire to go away when I have Italy coming up in a week. Plus, New York is actually pretty nice on holiday weekends ‚Äî as long as you stick to places where tourists don‚Äôt go. It‚Äôs calmer, airier, more peaceful. And even as I type this out in busy SoHo (this pic is from Battery Park City a year ago), I‚Äôm eager to get back to m fun neighborhood bars in my untouristy corner of Harlem. ‚ú® Where are you spending the weekend?

I am in hardcore ITALY planning mode! üáÆüáπ A week from today I fly to Milan and commence a 3-week journey through one of my favorite countries on the planet. I‚Äôll be visiting Trentino to speak at the @traverseevents conference ‚Äî a new region! I‚Äôll be visiting new areas like the Dolomites, Lake Como, Torino, and Verona, and returning to Bologna and Milan. üç∑ Even though I have a goal of visiting 100+ countries (and am currently at 79), I will continue visiting Italy again and again. It is THAT good. The fashion. The beauty. The food and the wine. The immaculately groomed men who spend a little too much time on their appearance. üòâ I can‚Äôt wait. This trip is going to be amazing. üçï Have you been to #Italy? Have any tips for me?

WHAT THE HELL IS GOING ON?! ü§£ The other night a K train arrived at Canal St. on the C platform. THE K TRAIN DOES NOT EXIST. So I quickly grabbed a selfie with it (I mean, my name is Kate, I had to!) before it rolled away. üöà Then I got on Wikipedia. There USED to be a K train ‚Äî but it was discontinued in December 1988. Trains used to have single letters if they were local and double if they were express, but they later scraped that system. Most strangely, today‚Äôs C trains still contain those signs predating 1988, and they are inside the trains of today. Some pranksters got a hex key and turned it until it brought up the K signs. Isn‚Äôt that insane? These trains still contain signs FROM WHEN REAGAN WAS PRESIDENT. How? How?!?! THIS IS SOME HOT TUB TIME MACHINE BULLSHIT!!! ‚òÑÔ∏è Also, I posted this to the NYC subreddit and it became my top post ever. Yay! But if anything, it once again highlights how disastrous @nygovcuomo has been for the subway. Stop giving our subway money away to upstaters, dude. This was a funny moment but our subway is in a state of emergency and it‚Äôs only going to get worse.‚ú® Have you ever seen a glitch in the matrix in real life?

Sometimes a sunset can be a REALLY pink sunset. üíïüå∏üëôThis is the view from #ShirleyHeights in #Antigua. Here‚Äôs a sunset photography tip I got from @speakeasytravel on a trip to Tuscany back in 2013: turn the white balance onto ‚Äúshade‚Äù and see what happens. If it‚Äôs a blue sunset, it will warm it up nicely; if it‚Äôs looking pink, it will turn REALLY pink. It was a cloudy night at Shirley Heights, not the bright blue seascape I had hoped for, but playing with the white balance gave me some awesome sunset pictures. Definitely the most photogenic spot on the island! #loveantiguabarbuda #whatcoollookslike Do you ever tweak your sunset photos, or so you like to keep them natural?

Weird question ‚Äî do you guys remember ‚ÄúSharon, Lois and Bram‚Äù? It was a kids‚Äô show in the early 90s. It was on Nickelodeon. The three adults would sing and play guitar and do sketches for kids. And Lois almost always wore off-the-shoulder dresses with a ruffly panel hanging over the bust ‚Äî exactly like this one. So when these dresses came back into style, I laughed ‚Äî these are Lois dresses! I never thought I would be sampling Lois‚Äôs wardrobe at the age of 34. Just hand me a tambourine! I guess everything comes back eventually. üëó This dress is a rental from Rent the Runway by @amandauprichard. I fucking LOVED IT, even though it had to be pinned to within an inch of its life. ü§£ And I wore it on our catamaran cruise from St. John‚Äôs in #Antigua. SUCH a fun night, my favorite activity in Antigua. When you‚Äôre heading out on a boat, you want a dress that looks gorgeous in a breeze! #LoveAntiguaBarbuda #whatcoollookslike üåà Do you remember that show or am I seriously showing my age here??

I should totally try to sell this pineapple pic from #Antigua. I swear I‚Äôve seen tons like it at West Elm. üçç Antigua has the sweetest, most delicious pineapples in the world ‚Äî but my favorite pineapple tip actually comes from a trip to Louisiana a few years ago. Wealthy families would welcome you with a pineapple upon arrival ‚Äî after all, it‚Äôs a symbol of welcome. But if you received a pineapple on your breakfast tray the next morning, the message was a discreet YOU BEST BE LEAVING. ü§£ Subtle and vicious. #üçç #loveantiguabarbuda #whatcoollookslike üå¥ Would you hang a print of this photo on your wall?
